SIMPLE: witty
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Witty
<hw>Wit"ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <amorph>[<pos>Compar.</pos>
<adjf>Wittier</adjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>superl.</pos>
<adjf>Wittiest</adjf>.]</amorph> <ety>[AS. <ets>witig</ets>,
<ets>wittig</ets>. See <er>Wit</er>, <pos>n.</pos>]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Possessed of wit; knowing; wise; skillful;
judicious; clever; cunning.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> ⟦ldquo⟧The
deep-revolving <xex>witty</xex> Buckingham.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Especially, possessing wit or humor; good at
repartee; droll; facetious; sometimes, sarcastic; <as>as, a
<ex>witty</ex> remark, poem, and the like</as>.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧Honeycomb,
who was so unmercifully <xex>witty</xex> upon the women.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Addison.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Acute; smart; sharp; arch; keen; facetious;
amusing; humorous; satirical; ironical; taunting.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Witwall</ent>⟦br⟧
